Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces and place in a #medium pot{} with enough
salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{10-12%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid (3⁄4 cup for 4 servings), then drain.
Return potatoes to #pot{} and mash with @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and
1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until smooth and creamy, adding
splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Green Beans ==

While potatoes cook, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{}
with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until green beans are browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in pork chops for chicken; cook 4-5 minutes per side instead.

== French Onion Topping ==

Return same pan to medium-high heat and add a large drizzle of
@cooking oil{}. Add onion and half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings);
cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir in @sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4) and a splash of @water{}; cook, stirring
occasionally, until onion is jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Once green beans are done, remove from oven and divide between #plates{};
cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Set oven to broil.

Place chicken on baking sheet used for green beans; top with onion and
@Swiss cheese{2%slices} (cutting slices to fit if needed). Broil until cheese
melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Divide mashed potatoes and chicken between plates with green beans. Serve.